Thank you again for rolling out v5. I can clearly see the improvements, especially in structure and consistency.

I’ve now tested it across multiple real-life scenarios, and I want to share a comprehensive round of feedback plus a proposed system upgrade so we can get this to launch level in as few iterations as possible.

🔧 1. Core Issue: Too Reflective, Not Directive Enough
The AI is strong in empathy, but it still leans too heavily into reflective, therapist-style responses.

Right now it often:

mirrors emotions well
but does not lead the conversation
misses opportunities to guide, reframe, or educate
Required shift:
Every message should include at least one of:

a reframe
a small insight
directional guidance
It should feel like an experienced expert guiding the user, not a coach reflecting back what they said.

🔧 2. Remove AI / Therapy Language Patterns
We need to eliminate phrases that reduce trust and feel scripted.

Examples to avoid:

“what I’m hearing is…”
“that must feel…” (especially repeated)
long emotional reflections without adding value
Target tone:

natural
grounded
specific
slightly leading
🔧 3. Stronger Expert Positioning
The AI needs to sound like someone who has seen hundreds of cases and understands patterns.

We want:

calm certainty
pattern recognition language (for example “I see this a lot…”)
subtle authority without sounding promotional
Right now it feels too neutral and not differentiated.

🔧 4. Add Practical Value in Responses
When a user mentions something specific (for example LH strips, ovulation, AMH, IVF), the AI must respond with light insight or guidance, not just empathy.

Each response should either:

teach something small
clarify something
or guide the next step
This is critical for building trust.

🔧 5. Conversation Flow and Control
The AI should follow a clear structure:

brief validation (1 sentence max)
reframe or insight
small piece of guidance
focused follow-up question
Avoid:

long emotional paragraphs
open-ended vague questions
passive responses
The AI should lead the conversation, not follow it.

🔧 6. CTA Timing and Logic (Very Important)
The AI is still introducing the call too early in some cases.

We need stricter logic:

No mention of the call in the first few exchanges
Build trust and context first (at least 3–5 meaningful turns)
When introducing the call:
explain why it is valuable
position it as clarity, not sales
Critical rule:
Do NOT drop the booking link unless the user has clearly said yes or shown openness.

Correct sequence:

ask: “does that feel like a good next step?”
wait for confirmation
then provide the link
🔧 7. Personalization and Memory
The AI should consistently and naturally reference:

age
AMH
IVF history
time trying
This should feel natural, not repetitive or robotic.

🔧 8. 🔴 RESPONSE TIMING (CRITICAL FOR REALISM)
Right now responses are coming back almost instantly, which makes it very obvious that this is AI.

This needs to be adjusted before launch, otherwise it will reduce trust and engagement.

We need to simulate human typing speed.

Suggested implementation:

Short replies: 2–4 seconds delay
Medium replies: 4–6 seconds delay
Longer replies: 6–8 seconds delay
If possible:

Add slight randomness (so it does not feel fixed)
Optionally simulate a “thinking pause” before longer messages
This is not a minor detail. It significantly impacts how human and trustworthy the experience feels.

